text: Gothic door of Romanesque priory church in Froville the Froville Arcade at the Cloisters Museum, NYC Froville is a commune in the Meurthe-et-Moselle department in north-eastern France. It is noted for its romanesque church, with a gothic cloister, part of which was moved to the Cloisters Museum of New York City. Froville hosts a festival of sacred and baroque music. ==See also== *Communes of the Meurthe-et-Moselle department ==External links== * Froville festival of sacred and baroque music Category:Communes of Meurthe-et-Moselle
title: Froville
